node.text:
Finally some gratitude after a rescue 😊 This little guy had thin fishing line cutting into his neck. Right from the moment I saw him he was quite chilled compared to most, and after release he just hung around and even came back to me. A very cool experience. He was one of 6 rescues today for #100sealsfortime with @oceanconservationnamibia. That brings us to 35 rescues in 12 days. Thanks so everyone that has supported our cause so far. It really helps to keep us out there doing our thing 🙏

📽 @namib_naude

node.text:
Autumn walks in Finland 🍁✨ 

Have you ever visited this country in the fall season before?

Fall leaf colors, also known as "Ruska" to locals, characterises this season months in Finland. Landscapes are painted in vivid yellows, reds and browns, making every walk and hike even more magical.

Which picture is your favorite? Tag someone who loves @nature!

📷 @jukkarisikko
📍Finland

node.text:
Canada's breathtaking spots via @mthiessen. 🌈 From natural landscapes to clean and modern cities, Canada is as picturesque as it gets when it comes to spectacular scenery. 🇨🇦

Swipe through and marvel at these incredible places! Save this post for reference when you visit Canada. 📝

@Nature Destinations in Canada
1-3. Niagara Falls, Ontario
4. Spirit Island, Alberta
5. Jasper, Alberta
6. Golden fields near Stony Plain, Alberta
7. Emerald Lake, British Columbia
8. Moraine Lake Road, Alberta
9. Lake Louise, Alberta
10. Edmonton, Alberta

Which one is your favorite? 👇

📸 @mthiessen
📍 Canada
